Class ExperimentController

  • java.lang.Object
    • ExperimentController

  • public class ExperimentController
extends java.lang.Object
    This class serves as the test environment. Through use of this class the user may test the Java API TreeMap. The user may also specify the number of iterations and how large the map will be.
    Author:
    Craig Lombardo

      • timeAddTreeSet

        public long timeAddTreeSet(int numberOfItems,
                           int seed)
        This method will be used to return the total amount of time taken for the computer to add a number of elements to the tree.
        Parameters:
        numberOfItems - This is an integer value of how many items will be added to the tree.
        seed - An integer value used to generate pseudorandom numbers.
        Returns:
        long This method returns a long which corresponds to the time taken,in ms, to add all of the elements.

      • runTimeAddTreeSet

        public java.lang.String runTimeAddTreeSet(int number)
        This method runs the method timeAddTreeSet a specified number of times. The program increments the number of added elements by 1000000 each time. This method averages five runs of the returned values for timeAddTreeSet.
        Parameters:
        number - The number of trials to run.
        Returns:
        String The average run times of the tests, put in a format that is beneficial for use with .csv files.

      • timeFindTreeSet

        public long timeFindTreeSet(int numberOfItems,
                            int seed)
        This method will be used to return the total amount of time taken for the computer to find an element in the TreeMap.
        Parameters:
        numberOfItems - This is an integer value of how many items will be added to Tree the search is conducted.
        seed - An integer value used to generate pseudorandom numbers.
        Returns:
        long This method returns a long which corresponds to the time taken,in ns, to find an element in the Tree.

      • runTimeFindTreeSet

        public java.lang.String runTimeFindTreeSet(int number)
        This method runs the method myTimeFindSecond a specified number of times. The program increments the number of added elements by 1000000 each time. This method averages five runs of the returned values for timeFindTreeSet.
        Parameters:
        number - The number of trials to run.
        Returns:
        String The average run times of the tests, put in a format that is beneficial for use with .csv files.

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        The main method is used so the program may be run through a console. This is beneficial as the output can easily be piped to a .csv file
        Parameters:
        args - Argument 1 (args[0]) is the test type, either "addTree" or "findTree". Argument 1 (args[1]) is the number passed into the appropriate run second test. It is important to note that responses other than "addTree" or "findTree", or a valid number for the second argument will not lead to desired results.
